<ColorLayout title="About | Ben's Colors" currentPage="about">
  <div class="about-page">
    <h1><strong>about</strong> ben's colors</h1>
    
    <p>
      This is a color palette explorer and reference tool built by Ben Cuan. 
      It was created as part of a <a href="https://bencuan.me/blog/vibe25">State of Vibe Coding evaluation</a> 
      to test the capabilities of modern AI coding assistants.
    </p>

    <p>
      The color data is sourced from <a href="https://github.com/jacobbubu/acb">this repository</a>, 
      which contains Adobe Color Book (.acb) files converted to JSON format. 
      You can find the processed color books <a href="https://github.com/64bitpandas/bencuan.me/tree/main/src/color-books">here</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      The default header color is <a href="https://catppuccin.com/">Catppuccin blue</a>, 
      a beautiful blue from the Catppuccin color palette.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="https://bencuan.me">Click here</a> to go back to the main bencuan.me site.
    </p>

